div.div: Commented on #941 Cycle during CoercionToJson for attribute from recursive attrset

It is because printer has naive implementation: https://github.com/haskell-nix/hnix/blob/99a38c40f29dd5b0d15e92311d418e7133a0f5d0/main/Main.hs#L157-L163 HNix by default is in lazy mode & that is not handled in the output, that is why: cabal v2-run hnix -- --eval sample.nix -A x "" Strict version prints, but --json catches the control flow before --strict and they implemented as independent paths, so --json is lazy and because we not yet printing the lazy values out - this happens. So #777 is related, and then options as combinators for parser.

Still, the confusion remains. A "" without --strict is just a thunk (some unevaluated code). Nix makes a better job at highlighting that by calling them <code>.
Yes. https://github.com/haskell-nix/hnix/pull/824, so it was worse , after that PR & other one where I moved this particular stub beck to, since it is what opaque is for. The first stage of the problem is semantic. opaque got used in removeEffects, it is where the reported output comes from. I remember reading the code or related code that causes this, indeed, when the expression is evaluated, if --json flag is present - the code strips evaluation from effects. It is definitely tied to removeEffects use, queryM if thunk is not computed returns default value (the first arg). That is what happening.
